review_blob: Strong, dark, hearty, with a taste of caramel, coffee, and nasty goodness.  Poured dark and hearty from the bottle.  The aroma was at once strong and inviting, like that dude who always steals your chick at the party.  Mean afterkick.
I liked this dark beer.  The dark ale pours deep from the brown bottle.  The flavor is deep and woody with a taste that reminds me of sauna.  A dark chocolate nutty flavor.
I liked this one.  It is much better than the other mass-bottled lime-flavored beers.  i like the blue agava flavor.  The base beer is pretty lousy.  The flavors bring it up slightly for me.
Very sweet, kind of champagne like.  coffee, chocolate.  Kind of like burnt smores.  Not bad. Comes with a kick.  One of the better dark stouts.
Tastes great cold, but has a subtle aftertaste.  Very strong body and bold expression.
I had this beer in a pub in Tongeren (Tongers) Belgium one year ago, and then recently discovered a source locally in the States.  It was good.
